com.unboundid.ldap.sdk.unboundidds.monitors

Class DiskSpaceUsageMonitorEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.unboundid.ldap.sdk.unboundidds.monitors.MonitorEntry
      • com.unboundid.ldap.sdk.unboundidds.monitors.DiskSpaceUsageMonitorEntry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    @NotMutable
@ThreadSafety(level=COMPLETELY_THREADSAFE)
public final class DiskSpaceUsageMonitorEntry
extends MonitorEntry
    This class defines a monitor entry that provides information about the disk space usage of the Directory Server.
    NOTE: This class, and other classes within the com.unboundid.ldap.sdk.unboundidds package structure, are only supported for use against Ping Identity, UnboundID, and Alcatel-Lucent 8661 server products. These classes provide support for proprietary functionality or for external specifications that are not considered stable or mature enough to be guaranteed to work in an interoperable way with other types of LDAP servers.

    The server should present at most one disk space usage monitor entry. It can be retrieved using the MonitorManager.getDiskSpaceUsageMonitorEntry(com.unboundid.ldap.sdk.LDAPConnection) method. The getDiskSpaceInfo() method may be used to retrieve information about the components which may consume significant amounts of disk space, and the getCurrentState() method may be used to obtain the current state of the server. Alternately, this information may be accessed using the generic API. See the MonitorManager class documentation for an example that demonstrates the use of the generic API for accessing monitor data.
